Description: Social location bookmarking
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: WhereMark lets users create, share, and like locations -  from anywhere. WhereMark provides a convenient and easy way to create location based information, save it, and share it with friends. In most basic terms, it is social location bookmarking. The service addresses the question "How do I share a location with my friends?". Once a location has been saved, you are only a click away from finding it again to share with friends or get directions. The web-based WhereMark service is available by using your Facebook login. Once logged in, users can search for places or find them on a map to create 'wheremarks'. These wheremarks can be kept private, shared with friends, or made public for anyone to see. All of the wheremarks that have been shared with you or created by you are always available - so that great bar you were at a month ago is always right at your fingertips. And your information is always private - you control exactly who gets to see each wheremark. WhereMark launched an augmented reality app for the iPhone in December 2009, and currently is the process of integrating the social location bookmarking service with the app. WhereMark was founded by Kenneth Carter and Matt Tesch in June 2009 and is based in Northern Virginia.
Industry Groups: Data and Analytics, Hardware, Internet Services, Navigation and Mapping, Software

Headquarters Location: New Town, North Dakota, United States
Description: We are and oil and gas niche site designed to help businesses recruit the best talent for the oil and gas industry.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: We are and oil and gas niche site designed to help businesses recruit the best talent for the oil and gas industry. Similar to Monster.com and ZipRecruiter.com we are a job board specific to the industry. Our goal is to make it possible for businesses and potential employees alike easily find one another.  Ryan McMillan is an oil and gas recruiter for a booming oil service company out of Canada. During his time as a recruiter, he found that many sites offer various job categories. Yet, none or very few are specific to the oil and gas industry alone. By specializing in this niche market, both employers and potential candidates can focus on finding the right talent  or company to utilize their talents.  The idea for the site is simple. We will offer candidates the ability to post resumes and create a profile (similar to LinkedIn). These candidates will be able to apply for jobs posted by employers, yet it will be different than other sites. Candidates  will be able to subscribe to a featured candidate package where their profile will be features on the home page of the website.  Employers will also be able to create a business profile. This will offer them a chance to tell about their company  (benefits, salaries, locations, 401k, etc.).  Just like the features candidate, employers will also have the opportunity to purchase a featured employer package. This will display them on the home page on the opposite side of the featured candidate. Businesses will also be able to purchase job posting packages (5 for $100, 20 for $400, or unlimited monthly postings for $500 a month).  All candidate options will be free except the featured candidate profile. The ability to search jobs and post resumes will be a free service.  We are very excited about making this project a reality. We are currently applying for an LLC and working with developers to get the programming in order. We are expecting to go live with this project in 6 months or less.
Industry Groups: Administrative Services, Energy, Natural Resources, Professional Services

Description: Open vSwitch is a multilayer virtual switch licensed under the open source Apache 2.0 license.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Open vSwitch is a multilayer virtual switch licensed under the open source Apache 2.0 license. It is designed to enable massive network automation through programmatic extension, while still supporting standard management interfaces and protocols such as NetFlow, sFlow, IPFIX, RSPAN, CLI, LACP, and 802.1ag. It is also designed to support distribution across multiple physical servers similar to VMware’s vNetwork distributed vswitch or Cisco’s Nexus 1000V. Open vSwitch can operate both as a soft switch running within the hypervisor, and as the control stack for switching silicon. It has been ported to multiple virtualization platforms and switching chipsets. It is the default switch in XenServer 6.0, the Xen cloud platform; and also supports Xen,KVM, Proxmox VE, and VirtualBox. It has also been integrated into many virtual management systems, including OpenStack,openQRM, OpenNebula, and oVirt. The kernel datapath is distributed with Linux, and packages are available for Ubuntu, Debian, and Fedora. Open vSwitch is also supported on FreeBSD and NetBSD. Open vSwitch hosts a number of different mailing lists, including announce: to announce new versions of Open vSwitch; discuss: to discuss plans and design decisions for Open vSwitch; dev: to discuss development and review code before being committed; git: hooks into Open vSwitch’s version control system to receive commits; build: hooks into Open vSwitch’s continuous integration system to receive build reports; and security@openvswitch.org: a list for submitting security vulnerabilities to the security team.

Full Description: Kojami transforms ANY event into an Interactive, Media Capable, Mobile Experience for Event Organizers and Mobile Phone Users Kojami Inc, a mobile-centric technology company has launched its offering of a mobile event management system into public beta.  Kojami is a mobile solution that captures the power of mobile marketing to enhance the event industry for both organizers and attendees. For event organizers, the service is a cost-effective way to create, manage and market events, as well as provide real time interaction with their attendees. Their attendees can utilize Kojami to simply discover, shove, and experience events at anytime, from anywhere on any smartphone, with the touch of a finger. With millions of individuals, organizations, small businesses and corporations seeking or creating events every day, marketing professionals need to shorten the gap between the moment attendees learn about an event and when they decide to take action.  The industry has lacked a comprehensive mobile solution, but with the number of smartphones predicted to quadruple to an estimated 200 million in USA or more by 2014, Kojami has created an effective mobile system that enhances the entire event cycle for organizers from creation and planning, through tracking and communication, to post evaluation and reporting. Kojami features include; An Events Search Engine allows users to find events based on date, time, location and category and then receive future alerts for their preferred events. On the day and time of event, a GPS feature navigates users to the venue easily. Organizers and attendees can upload photos and video to create an interactive experience, motivating others to join event in real-time. Additionally, all users can instantly forwardmobile events to other smartphones, email addresses and social networks. Attendees can also create a copy of the event and personalize it as their own sub-event to motivate personal networks to attend. Finally, a user-friendly Attendance Management Panel enables event organizers to communicate before, during and after the event with those that RSVP or have purchased tickets and manage participants during the event.  With Kojamiâ€™s streamlined and instantaneous process, events organizers can reach millions of potential attendees much more effectively and efficiently, while reducing that cost and preparation time. Visit kojami.com and see events currently being mobilized daily on Twitter.com/KojamiEvents.
